<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542109>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 1. Diagnostic characters of the Dichotomius (Luederwaldtinia) agenor species group. A–D. Male diverse trituberculate fronto-clypeal carina shapes. A. D. tristis (Luederwaldt, 1923). B. D. amplicollis (Harold, 1869). C. D. belus (Harold, 1880). D. D. validipilosus (Luederwaldt, 1931). E–F. Female fronto-clypeal carina. E. Bituberculate carina typical of D. tristis. F. Quadrituberculate carina typical of D. amplicollis." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4542109/files/figure.png" .

