<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542113>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 3. Dichotomius agenor (Harold, 1869). A–B. Dorsal habitus. A. ♁. B. ♀. C. Posterior view of the cephalic carina, concavity between the central and the lateral tubercles, apically emarginate. D. Lateral view of the pronotum, anterior declivity truncate. E. Ventral view of the metacoxa, displaying two rows of punctures on the posterior margin. F. Lateral view of the aedeagus. G. Ventral view of the aedeagus. H–I. Lamella copulatrix." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4542113/files/figure.png" .

